table.body:
Private schools (also known as 'independent schools') charge fees to attend instead of being funded by the government. Pupils don't have to follow the [national curriculum](/national-curriculum "National curriculum").

All private schools must be registered with the government and are inspected regularly.

##Reports on private schools

All school reports are published online by the organisation responsible for inspecting them. Find out from the school which organisation inspects them.

Half of all independent schools are inspected by [Ofsted.](http://www.ofsted.gov.uk/inspection-reports/find-inspection-report "find an inspection report"){:rel="external"}

The [Independent Schools Inspectorate](http://www.isi.net/reports/ "Independent Schools Inspectorate reports"){:rel="external"} inspects schools that are members of the Independent Schools Council.

The [Bridge Schools Inspectorate](http://www.bridgeschoolsinspectorate.co.uk/find_a_school "Bridge Schools Inspectorate reports"){:rel="external"} inspects schools that are members of the [Christian Schools' Trust](http://www.christianschoolstrust.co.uk/ "Christian Schools' Trust"){:rel="external"} or the [Association of Muslim Schools.](http://www.ams-uk.org/ "Association of Muslim Schools"){:rel="external"}

Some other schools are inspected by the [School Inspection Service.](http://www.schoolinspectionservice.co.uk/school_reports.php "School Inspection Service"){:rel="external"}

##Special educational needs

There are also private [schools which specialise](http://www.education.gov.uk/childrenandyoungpeople/send/sen/a0013111/independent-special-schools "Independent special schools"){:rel="external"} in teaching children with special educational needs.
